  "description": "The Crips are a primarily African-American alliance of street gangs founded in Los Angeles in 1969 by Raymond Washington and Stanley Williams. With 30,000-35,000 members in 800 sets across 41 US states, they are one of the largest and most violent gang associations in the United States. Members have traditionally worn blue since 1973 (in tribute to founding member Curtis 'Buddha' Morrow who was killed that year). The Crips' internal rivalries are as deadly as their war with the Bloods — the Rollin 60s vs Eight Tray Gangster Crips feud (since 1979) caused the Hoovers to split off entirely. Their growth was fueled by the crack cocaine epidemic of the 1980s. They maintain an alliance with the Folk Nation in prisons known as '8-ball.'",
